item.description: Certifi: Python SSL Certificates Certifi is a carefully curated collection of Root Certificates for validating the trustworthiness of SSL certificates while verifying the identity of TLS hosts. It has been extracted from the Requests project. Installation certifi is available on PyPI. Simply install it with pip: $ pip install certifi Usage To reference the installed certificate authority (CA) bundle, you can use the built-in function: >>> import certifi >>> certifi.
